5:
To the greatest swordsman I know,
whom I treasure greatly... From your
brother... Well, this isn't like him in the
slightest.
8: I suppose I should be on my way.
21: Hehe, who did you think it was?
24:
Being oblivious to your surroundings
will only cause trouble, Sir Alk.
Understood?
33:
You're certainly dressed up. What's

40:
Seeing as Ciel is now leader of the
Tris family, I felt it necessary to

53: What do you think, Sir Alk?
63:
...Do you not have anything else to
say?
73: Oh, Lady Stella, I love you so much.
77: Hm? Ah, yes... I love you too.
81:
Now then, I shall be off. I will be back

84:
I expect to see you later for a

89:
Ah, okay, I'll be sure to mentally

93: Why didn't she ask for my opinion?
102: What is the meaning of this, Ciel?
106:
Apologies, Cel, but our forces have
grown complacent and arrogant as
of late. They could do with a little
humbling...
108:
Especially from someone of your
caliber of skill.
112:
Ha! Once I'm done with you, next is
Sir Cieâ€”
116:
Your manners could use refinement,
in addition to your poor
swordsmanship.
133:
Good grief. If I had known this was
your plan, I would have come in my
normal attire.
136:
Heh. Isn't it nice to dress up on
occasion? Besides, your current
outfit has nary a scratch nor tear.
141:
...Are you sure it was all right for me
to fight the knights?
144:
Father is not here. Neither are the
small-minded men too obsessed

147:
Have you any thoughts of returning
to Tris?
150:
No one here fears your return... As

152:
Above all else, we need you if we

156:
May I have some time to think about

160:
Of course. The partnership
ceremony has not even been held

168:
I never thought you'd be the one to
forget a sparring match.
173:
Ah... M-my apologies... It completely
slipped my mind...
182:
You know, Sir Alk, I may not look it,
but I was once an innocent, delicate
little girl.
188:
I was eight when I learned I could
wield a sword. I was twelve when I
first beat my brother. Both times... I
was just so happy...
190:
I thought my family would share in
my joy.
193:
What a fool I was. Even when I saw
the way my father looked at me the
day I defeated that dragon, I never
suspected the truth.
196:
That I was someone that did not
belong.
204:
Indeed it has. My brother has asked
me if I have any interest in returning
home.
207: He said... He needs my skills...
216:
I'll be honest, I'm not sure what to do.
Is it truly okay for me to return?
219: What do you think I should do, Sir Alk?
228:
No, wait! No doubt you will tell me to
do what feels right, correct?
236:
In that case, allow me to rephrase
the question...
240: Will you miss me if I'm gone, Sir Alk?
245: Huh?! What are you talking about?
248:
Of course I'd miss you. It'd be like
losing a teacher, a little sister, and a
friend all at once.
251:
That's quite the list of roles you've
given me.
254:
But thank you. Your comments are
duly noted.
257: It seems I have more thinking to do.
262:
Maybe I'll make something sweet
today.
